cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a method for up-sampling volumetric functions using generative neural networks. This involves working with 3D data and utilizing multiple passes to efficiently learn smaller sub-problems. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) followed by graphics (cs.GR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of adversarial networks and discriminators suggests a possible fit with neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) while the spatio-temporal supervision may align with social and information networks (cs.SI).
